 ## Interview Talking Points
 
-1. **"Walk me through attention math."** тАФ Q┬╖K^T gives raw relevance scores. Divide by тИЪd_k to prevent softmax saturation. Apply causal mask (-тИЮ for future tokens). Softmax normalizes each row to a probability distribution. Multiply by V to get a weighted blend of value vectors.
-
-2. **"Why scale by тИЪd_k?"** тАФ Dot product of d_k-dimensional vectors has variance тЙИ d_k. Without scaling, large scores push softmax to near-one-hot, killing gradients. Dividing by тИЪd_k normalizes variance back to ~1.
-
-3. **"How does the causal mask work?"** тАФ Set upper-triangle scores to -тИЮ before softmax. Since e^(-тИЮ)=0, future tokens get exactly zero attention weight. Not a deletion тАФ a mathematical zeroing via the softmax function.
-
-4. **"Why Q, K, V instead of just one matrix?"** тАФ K determines *why* a token is attended to (identity). V determines *what* information it transmits (payload). Decoupling these gives the model more expressiveness than K=V.
-
-5. **"Why Q/K norm but not V?"** тАФ Q┬╖K produces scores that go into softmax. Unstable magnitudes тЖТ attention collapse. V is only weighted-summed тАФ its magnitude IS the signal strength. Plus V flows into residual тЖТ LayerNorm anyway.
-
-6. **"GQA tradeoff?"** тАФ 16 Q heads (diverse questioning) share 8 KV heads (passive information). Halves KV cache with minimal quality loss. MQA (1 KV head) saves more but degrades quality тАФ GQA is the sweet spot.
-
-7. **"Prefill vs decode kernel?"** тАФ Prefill: all tokens available, compute-bound, uses `flash_attn_varlen_func`. Decode: 1 new token reads entire KV cache, memory-bound, uses `flash_attn_with_kvcache`. Different bottlenecks тЖТ different kernels.
-
-8. **"How does attention parallelize?"** тАФ Heads are independent тЖТ split across GPUs (ColumnParallel for QKV). Each GPU computes its heads locally. Only o_proj needs all_reduce (RowParallel). KV cache is also sharded тАФ no duplication.
+1. **Explain attention end-to-end.** Q┬╖K^T scores relevance; divide by тИЪd_k to prevent softmax saturation (variance of dot product тЙИ d_k without scaling тЖТ near-one-hot тЖТ dead gradients). Apply causal mask (upper triangle = -тИЮ so e^(-тИЮ)=0). Softmax normalizes each row тЖТ probability distribution. Multiply by V тЖТ weighted blend of value vectors. Total: score тЖТ scale тЖТ mask тЖТ normalize тЖТ blend.
+
+2. **GQA vs MHA vs MQA.** MHA: H_q=H_kv (full heads, max quality, max KV memory). MQA: H_kv=1 (minimum memory, quality degrades). GQA: H_kv=H_q/G (sweet spot). Qwen3-0.6B uses 16Q/8KV тЖТ halves KV cache vs MHA. Memory formula: `H_kv ├Ч d_k ├Ч 2 ├Ч dtype_bytes` per token per layer. At 28 layers, 4096 tokens: MHAтЙИ900MB, GQAтЙИ450MB. Q heads still diverse (different search strategies); KV heads are passive providers shared by a group тАФ like one book read by multiple readers focusing on different passages.
+
+3. **Prefill vs decode kernel choice.** Prefill: all N tokens' QKV available simultaneously, O(N┬▓┬╖d_k) compute тЖТ **compute-bound** тЖТ use `flash_attn_varlen_func` (fused tiled matmul, supports variable-length packed sequences for continuous batching). Decode: only 1 new Q token, must read all N cached KV from HBM тЖТ O(N┬╖d_k) compute but O(N┬╖H_kv┬╖d_k┬╖bytes) memory read тЖТ **memory-bound** тЖТ use `flash_attn_with_kvcache` (optimized for KV cache scatter reads via block_table). Different arithmetic intensity тЖТ different kernels.
+
+4. **Why Q, K, V instead of one matrix?** K = identity broadcast (why attended to). V = information payload (what is transmitted). Decoupling lets a token be found for one reason (syntactic role) but transmit different content (semantic meaning). K=V collapses these, limiting expressiveness.
+
+5. **Why Q/K norm but not V?** Q┬╖K dot products feed softmax тАФ unstable magnitudes cause attention collapse or saturation. V is only linearly combined; its magnitude carries signal strength. V also flows into residual stream тЖТ hit by LayerNorm downstream anyway.
+
+6. **How does attention parallelize with TP?** Heads are independent тЖТ QKV ColumnParallel (each GPU owns H_q/tp and H_kv/tp heads, zero communication). Each GPU computes its heads fully locally. o_proj RowParallel + all_reduce to sum partial outputs. KV cache sharded: GPU i caches only its H_kv/tp heads тАФ no duplication. Net: 1 all_reduce per attention block.
+
+7. **Causal mask mechanism.** Upper-triangle of score matrix set to -тИЮ before softmax. e^(-тИЮ)=0 тЖТ future tokens receive exactly zero weight. Not a deletion тАФ a mathematical zeroing. During prefill the full causal mask applies; during decode the single new token always attends to all cached positions (no masking needed for past tokens).
 
