-
-8. **Embedding vs LM head: same weights, different collective ops тАФ why?** Embedding uses `all_reduce` (sum): vocabulary rows are sharded, so only one GPU has the real embedding for a given token, others contribute zeros тАФ summing reconstructs the correct vector. LM head uses `gather + concat`: each GPU computes logits for its vocabulary slice тАФ summing would mix scores for *different* tokens, corrupting the distribution.
