-2. **GQA vs MHA тАФ trade-offs.** MHA: `num_q_heads == num_kv_heads` (16/16 here if full). GQA: fewer KV heads (8 here), multiple Q heads share one KV head. KV cache shrinks by `num_kv_heads / num_q_heads` тАФ 0.5├Ч here, 8├Ч for Llama 3 70B. Quality loss is minimal: KV heads still carry full `head_dim=64` information. MQA (1 KV head) is the extreme; GQA is the generalisation. Decode throughput improves because KV cache memory bandwidth is the bottleneck.
-
-3. **RMSNorm vs LayerNorm тАФ trade-offs and why RMSNorm won.** RMSNorm drops mean subtraction and the ╬▓ parameter. Ablations show re-centering is unnecessary тАФ residual stream has near-zero mean at init. Result: ~10тАУ15% faster, same quality. LayerNorm has ╬│+╬▓ (2├Ч hidden_dim params); RMSNorm has ╬│ only. Pre-Norm placement keeps the residual stream un-normalized, giving gradients a clean path back to the embedding.
