+## Interview Talking Points
+
+1. **Explain GQA.** GQA uses fewer KV heads than Q heads тАФ here 8 KV vs 16 Q, so two Q heads share one KV head. KV cache shrinks by `num_kv_heads/num_q_heads` (0.5├Ч here, 8├Ч for Llama 3 70B). Quality loss is minimal; MQA (1 KV head) is the extreme case.
+
+2. **RMSNorm vs LayerNorm trade-offs.** RMSNorm drops mean subtraction and ╬▓. Ablations show re-centering is unnecessary тАФ ~10тАУ15% faster, same quality. Pre-Norm placement keeps the residual stream un-normalized, giving gradients a clean path back to the embedding.
+
+3. **Why Q/K norm but not V norm?** Q and K drive `QKс╡А/тИЪd_k` тАФ high L2 norm explodes scores, saturates softmax, kills gradients (attention collapse). V is only weighted-summed; normalizing it destroys semantic magnitude for no benefit.
+
+4. **SwiGLU mechanics.** `W_down(SiLU(W_gate(x)) ├Ч W_up(x))`. Gate learns *whether* a feature fires; up learns *what* it is. SiLU has non-zero gradient everywhere (no dying neurons). Three matrices at `8d/3` match 2-matrix 4├Ч FFN param count.
+
+5. **TP ColumnтЖТRow pattern.** ColumnParallel (QKV, gate+up): each GPU computes its output slice independently тАФ zero communication. RowParallel (o_proj, down_proj): one `all_reduce` to sum partials. Total: **2 all_reduces per decoder layer**.
+
+6. **Why fuse QKV / gate+up?** One large matmul beats three small ones: better Tensor Core utilization, fewer kernel launches, one memory round-trip. `SiluAndMul` further fuses chunk+SiLU+multiply into one compiled kernel.
+
+7. **Walk me through a decoder layer.** `hidden тЖТ RMSNorm тЖТ QKV (fused) тЖТ per-head Q/K norm тЖТ RoPE тЖТ flash_attn (KV cache) тЖТ o_proj + residual тЖТ RMSNorm тЖТ gate_up (fused) тЖТ SiluAndMul тЖТ down_proj + residual тЖТ output.`
 
