+7. **When would you choose ALiBi vs RoPE for long-context?** Prefer ALiBi when you need strong out-of-the-box extrapolation with zero fine-tuning тАФ its fixed linear distance penalty degrades gracefully beyond training length. Prefer RoPE when (a) the model will be fine-tuned on longer sequences (RoPE's frequency scaling via higher `base` or YaRN adapts well), (b) you need tasks requiring long-range semantic dependencies (ALiBi's hard linear penalty can hurt retrieval-style attention over very distant tokens), or (c) you are using a pretrained model ecosystem (LLaMA, Mistral, Gemma) already built on RoPE where switching would require retraining from scratch.
